this is everytime we use for vault opening,[open new terminal and run below command]

export VAULT_ADDR='http://127.0.0.1:8200'
export VAULT_TOKEN='root'

Step 1 — Create config file:
sudo mkdir -p /opt/vault/data
sudo nano /etc/vault.hcl
Add this:
storage "file" {
  path = "/opt/vault/data"
}

listener "tcp" {
  address     = "0.0.0.0:8200"
  tls_disable = true
}

ui = true
Step 2 — Start Vault with config:
sudo vault server -config=/etc/vault.hcl &
Step 3 — Initialize Vault:
export VAULT_ADDR='http://127.0.0.1:8200'
vault operator init
⚠️ Save the Unseal Keys and Root Token shown — very important!
Step 4 — Unseal Vault:
vault operator unseal  # Run 3 times with 3 different keys
Step 5 — Login:
vault login <your-root-token>
Step 6 — Add secrets again:
vault kv put secret/harbor \
  username=admin \
  password=YourPassword

vault kv put secret/sonarqube \
  token=YourToken
Now secrets never delete even after restart! ✅
